President Obama expresses his condolences on the passing of Ann Nixon Cooper. He highlights her life of service, from her beginnings in Tennessee to her impact on the Atlanta community. He acknowledges her involvement in various organizations and her dedication to her family. President Obama also mentions that Ann lived through significant moments in American history and emphasizes the importance of her casting a vote in the 2008 election. He concludes by offering his condolences to all who loved Ann and celebrating her lasting impact on her family, community, and the nation.